mand into the stdin of the next. (<code>do-something | something else</code>)</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-21T21:54:16.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"RyanZim/awesome-npm-scripts","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cross-platform Shell Reference</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Use <code>></code> to write the stdout of a command to a file. (<code>do-something > file</code>)</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-21T21:54:16.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"RyanZim/awesome-npm-scripts","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cross-platform Shell Reference</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Use <code>&#x3C;</code> to send the contents of a file to a command's stdin. (<code>command &#x3C; file</code>)</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-21T21:54:16.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"RyanZim/awesome-npm-scripts","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cross-platform Shell Reference</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Use <code>cd &#x3C;dir></code> to change the current working directory to <code>&#x3C;dir></code>. Note that <code>cd</code> alone prints the current working directory on windows, but changes the working directory to <code>~</code> on *nix.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-21T21:54:16.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"rayokota/awesome-hbase","categoryHTML":"<h2>Projects</h2><h3>Integrations</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://pulsar.apache.org/docs/en/io-hbase/\">Pulsar</a> - HBase connector for Pulsar.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-21T21:32:42.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"veggiemonk/awesome-docker","categoryHTML":"<h2>Services based on Docker (💲)</h2><h3>CI Services</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://semaphoreci.com/\">Semaphore CI</a> 💲 — A high-performance cloud solution that makes it easy to build, test and ship your containers to production.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-21T19:59:18.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"awesome-selfhosted/awesome-selfhosted","categoryHTML":"<h2>Bookmarks and Link Sharing</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jonschoning/espial\">Espial</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jonschoning/espial\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px